{
  "texts": [
    "During Routing, the request is directed to a target cluster according to the active scheduling policy.",
    "In Batching, it is placed into a queue and grouped with other requests for prefill or decode operations.",
    "During Speculation, the active γ policy determines the window size γ and execution mode; in distributed mode, a drafter device generates γ speculative tokens and transmits them to the target for verification.",
    "In Verification, the target server compares these tokens with its own predictions.",
    "Accepted tokens advance the generated sequence, while mismatched tokens are corrected using the target's prediction, and any remaining speculative tokens are discarded."
  ]
}